HEADWORD: Ramsted
<hw>Ram"sted</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧m"st⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A yellow-flowered weed; -- so named from a Mr.
Ramsted who introduced it into Pennsylvania. See <er>Toad flax</er>.
Called also <altname>Ramsted weed</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

